<subSubSection id="9C8860A05911A638FF77C2A285A4FCD5" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" type="description">
<paragraph id="D42D332B5911A638FF77C2A286E1FDF5" blockId="2.[166,1225,399,874]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">The species belongs to the striate morphotype. The amoeba is elongated oval. There are several parallel dorsal folds (4–5) that extend along the cell from end to end. Hyaloplasm is undulating dorso-ventral crescent that makes up almost ¾ of the cell. There is singular large contractile vacuole of inconstant form. Cytoplasmic crystals are absent. The length of amoeba is 40–82 μm, the width is 20–40 μm, L/B ratio = 1.3–2.2. The diameter of a single nucleus is 8–12 μm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D42D332B5911A638FF77C16285F7FD75" blockId="2.[166,1225,399,874]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
Remarks: the species can be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="139248A85911A638FC66C1628335FDD6" authorityName="Fromentel" authorityYear="1874" box="[970,1115,591,617]" class="Lobosa" family="Thecamoebidae" genus="Thecamoeba" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Amoebida" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395911A638FC66C1628335FDD6" box="[970,1115,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Thecamoeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus by the shape and length of the cell, and vesicular nucleus with central nucleolus. The thin inner nuclear lamina is absent. The nucleus and nucleolus are distorted (
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5911A638FC77C1A2878FFD75" author="Smirnov, A. V. &amp; Goodkov, A. V." pageId="2" pageNumber="389" pagination="5 - 11" refId="ref2766" refString="Smirnov, A. V., Goodkov, A. V. 1993. Paradermamoeba valamo gen. n., sp. n. (Gymnamoebia, Thecamoebidae) - freshwater amoeba from bottom soil. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 72 (2), 5 - 11 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1993">Smirnov, Goodkov, 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5911A638FF40C1828602FD75" author="Page, F. C." box="[236,364,687,714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref2315" refString="Page, F. C. 1988. A new key to freshwater and soil gymnamoebae. Freshwater Biological Association. Ambleside, Cumbria, UK, 1 - 122." type="book chapter" year="1988">Page, 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5911A638FEDBC18285E2FD75" author="Page, F. C. &amp; Siemensma, F. J." box="[375,652,687,714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" pagination="3 - 170" refId="ref2346" refString="Page, F. C., Siemensma, F. J. 1991. Nackte Rhizopoda und Heliozoea (Protozoenfauna; Bd 2). Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart; New York, 3 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1991">Page, Siemensma, 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D42D332B5911A638FF77C1E286EDFCB5" blockId="2.[166,1225,399,874]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
Distribution: 
<taxonomicName id="139248A85911A638FE2DC1FD852AFD56" baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[385,580,719,745]" class="Lobosa" family="Thecamoebidae" genus="Thecamoeba" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Amoebida" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="quadrilineata">
<emphasis id="E6E6EF395911A638FE2DC1FD852AFD56" box="[385,580,719,745]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">T. quadrilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in Asia, Europe, and North America (
<bibRefCitation id="B0034EDA5911A638FB24C1E28619FCB5" author="Page, F. C. &amp; Siemensma, F. J." pageId="2" pageNumber="389" pagination="3 - 170" refId="ref2346" refString="Page, F. C., Siemensma, F. J. 1991. Nackte Rhizopoda und Heliozoea (Protozoenfauna; Bd 2). Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart; New York, 3 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1991">Page, Siemensma, 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D42D332B5911A638FF77C02285A4FCD5" blockId="2.[166,1225,399,874]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
<materialsCitation id="64FA39765911A638FF77C02285A8FCD5" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3757644303" county="Ruzhynsky District" location="Gorokhivsky District" municipality="Tsegiv village" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Volyn'">
